 environmental lens on the ways in which Zionism’s spatial ambitions and racial fantasies transformed the lives of humans and nonhumans in Palestine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aColonistszPalestinexAttitudes. 0aImmigrantszPalestinexHistoryy20th century. 0aJewsxColonizationzPalestine. 0aPublic opinionzPalestine. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520397255?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520397255423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520397255/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles